Brownstown Fire Department and First Responders
November 17, 2019 at 7:12 PM ·

Please join others in wearing red tomorrow to show our condolences for the Vandalia School District who lost four precious family members/friends in a tragic accident on Saturday. ❤️

Vandalia suffered the loss of 4 people in a horrific car crash Saturday as they were coming home from the playoff game. Mr. Randy Protz, the high school principal, lost his mother, father, and youngest daughter, Jenna. Jenna’s best friend, Holly Lidy, was also killed. They were both freshmen.

Please keep these families & the community in your prayers.

We received the following from the Oakland Christian church- 5TH QUARTER IS COMING BACK!!!!!
Oakland Christian Church have decided to start 5th Quarter up again. Our goal is to provide the students with a safe place to have fun and hang out after the varsity home games.
5th Quarter will be held at the Lake Park pavilion immediately following the games on August 30, September 13, and October 4 and 18. Jr. and Sr. High students from the Tri-County co-op are welcome to attend, and parents are invited as well. Games and snacks will be provided. Please join them for some after game activities.
